com.vmware.vcenter.trusted_infrastructure.trusted_clusters.kms

Interface ServicesAppliedConfig

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService, Service, ServicesAppliedConfigTypes
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ServicesAppliedConfigStub

    public interface ServicesAppliedConfig
extends Service, ServicesAppliedConfigTypes, com.vmware.vapi.internal.bindings.CompletionStageService
    The ServicesAppliedConfig interface provides information about the aggregate health of the applied Key Provider Service configuration on the Trusted Clusters. The desired state of the Key Provider Service is stored within vCenter, while the applied configuration is stored on the hosts in the cluster. The ServicesAppliedConfig interface is available for all clusters, not only Trusted Clusters. In such cases empty desired state is assumed, e.g. when an applied Key Provider Service configuration is found outside of a Trusted Cluster it is considered an ServicesAppliedConfigTypes.Health.ERROR. The ServicesAppliedConfig interface is able to put the applied Key Provider Service configuration into a consistent state when individual host configurations have diverged from the desired state. This interface was added in vSphere API 7.0.1.0.

        ServicesAppliedConfig.ListInvocation list(java.lang.String cluster)
        Returns basic information about the health of all Key Provider Service configurations applied to the cluster with respect to the desired state. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.1.0.

        Invocation Result:
        The health status for each applied configuration in the given cluster.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The ID of the cluster against which the operation will be executed. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        Returns:
        instance of ServicesAppliedConfig.ListInvocation which upon invoke executes the above described list operation. The operation result or the operation error will be stored in the CompletionStageFuture that invoke returns.
        Throws:
        Error - if there is a generic error.
        InvalidArgument - if the cluster ID is empty.
        NotFound - if no cluster corresponding to the given ID is found within this vCenter.
        ResourceBusy - if there are ongoing mutating operations.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.

        ServicesAppliedConfig.DeleteInvocation delete(java.lang.String cluster)
        Delete the Key Provider Service configuration that has been applied to the given cluster. This method has no affect on the desired state, it only removes applied Key Provider Service configuration from any Trusted Hosts within the given cluster. This method was added in vSphere API 7.0.1.0.
